## Conclusion: The Die’s Final Cruelty  
In the end, the **fair die** is humanity’s favorite liar—a beautiful paradox wrapped in plastic, forever promising fairness while quietly stacking the deck. It reflects our desperate need to believe in order within chaos, in control where there is none. You can calculate its probabilities, 3D-print it, or curse it for ruining your life, but it will always land on whatever it wants. As **Nietzsche** (probably) said, “God is dead, and he rolled a 1.” So embrace the absurdity, buy a new set of dice, and remember: the universe doesn’t care about your natural 20. [Philosophy of Chance](/Philosophy_of_Chance) exists to make this all sound profound. Now go lose money.